  "prompt_text": "Within the first 1.20 seconds, the white-haired warrior visibly yields backward from a two-handed push, makes exactly one short grounded recovery step, and then stabilizes. The black-armored warrior starts already close but not touching, drives forward from a planted stance along a chest-height force line, and places both palms on the white-haired warrior's upper torso. Only after palm contact do the receiver's chest and shoulders move backward; the front foot remains the support foot while the rear foot makes the single short backward recovery placement. Contact is readable by 0.50 seconds, the torso response follows immediately after contact, the recovery step completes by 1.20 seconds, and the stable result is readable by 1.50 seconds. After stabilization, preserve subtle living motion rather than a frozen pose. Cinematic fantasy in a rainy ancient temple courtyard with a wet stone floor, one continuous medium eye-level static shot, preserving both identities and readable screen direction. No punch, premature reaction, prolonged static contact, multiple steps, sliding, flight, fall, wall collision, extra subject, magic, injury, gore, camera movement, or scene change.",
